<Layout title="Ryukyuan Legend: If you played the Sanshin, you were called a loser | Unmuting Ryukyu">

	<article>

		<!-- ARTICLE HEADER -->
		<header style="padding:72px 32px 56px;background:#1C2C4F;position:relative;overflow:hidden;border-bottom:4px solid #8B1D25;">
			<div style="position:absolute;inset:-15px;z-index:0;background-image:url('https://img.youtube.com/vi/5Ng56rsjb4E/maxresdefault.jpg');background-size:cover;background-position:center;filter:blur(6px);opacity:0.35;"></div>
			<div style="position:absolute;inset:0;z-index:0;background:#1C2C4F;opacity:0.72;"></div>
			<div style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:5px;height:100%;background:#8B1D25;z-index:2;"></div>
			<div style="max-width:840px;margin:0 auto;position:relative;z-index:2;">
				<div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;margin-bottom:20px;">
					<span style="display:inline-block;background:#8B1D25;color:#F0EBE3;font-family:'Noto Sans JP',sans-serif;font-size:10px;font-weight:700;padding:4px 12px;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;">Ryukyuan Legend</span>
					<span style="color:#8B9BB8;font-family:'Noto Sans JP',sans-serif;font-size:12px;">February 2025</span>
				</div>
				<h1 style="font-family:'Shippori Mincho','Noto Serif JP',serif;font-size:clamp(26px,5vw,44px);font-weight:700;color:#F0EBE3;margin:0 0 20px 0;line-height:1.25;">"If you played the Sanshin... you were called a loser."</h1>
				<p style="color:#8B9BB8;font-family:'Noto Sans JP',sans-serif;font-size:13px;margin:0;">By <a href="/about/" style="color:#D4C9BC;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">Shohei Toguchi</a></p>
			</div>
		</header>

		<!-- ARTICLE BODY -->
		<div style="padding:72px 32px 96px;background:#F0EBE3;">
			<div style="max-width:720px;margin:0 auto;">

				<!-- Video Embed -->
				<div style="background:#0a0a0a;margin-bottom:56px;box-shadow:4px 4px 0px #1C2C4F;overflow:hidden;border:1px solid #D0C5BA;">
					<div style="position:relative;padding-bottom:56.25%;height:0;">
						<iframe style="position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;border:0;" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/5Ng56rsjb4E" title="Ryukyuan Legend: Sanshin" allow="accelerometer;autoplay;clipboard-write;encrypted-media;gyroscope;picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Article Content -->
				<div style="font-family:'Noto Serif JP',serif;color:#4A3F3B;font-size:16px;line-height:1.95;">

					<h2 style="font-family:'Shippori Mincho','Noto Serif JP',serif;font-size:22px;font-weight:700;color:#1C2C4F;margin:0 0 20px 0;padding-top:8px;border-top:2px solid #D0C5BA;">Introduction</h2>
					<p style="margin:0 0 24px 0;">
						Did you know that playing the Sanshin — the iconic three-stringed instrument of Okinawa — once carried a deep social stigma? In certain communities, picking up the Sanshin meant you were labeled as a "loser" or someone without ambition.
					</p>
					<p style="margin:0 0 40px 0;">
						This documentary uncovers the fascinating and painful history behind this stigma, tracing it from the class structures of the Ryukyu Kingdom to its modern-day redemption as a symbol of Okinawan pride.
					</p>

					<h2 style="font-family:'Shippori Mincho','Noto Serif JP',serif;font-size:22px;font-weight:700;color:#1C2C4F;margin:0 0 20px 0;padding-top:8px;border-top:2px solid #D0C5BA;">Key Takeaways</h2>

					<div style="background:#fff;border-left:4px solid #8B1D25;padding:20px 24px;margin-bottom:16px;">
						<p style="color:#8B1D25;font-family:'Noto Sans JP',sans-serif;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.15em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 8px 0;">The Sanshin's Royal Origins</p>
						<p style="color:#1C2C4F;font-family:'Noto Serif JP',serif;font-size:15px;line-height:1.85;margin:0;"><strong>The Sanshin was originally a courtly instrument.</strong> In the Ryukyu Kingdom, it graced royal courts and was part of formal ceremonies. Its roots trace back to the Chinese sanxian, adapted into a uniquely Okinawan instrument with a snakeskin-covered body and distinctive sound.</p>
					</div>
					<div style="background:#fff;border-left:4px solid #1C2C4F;padding:20px 24px;margin-bottom:16px;">
						<p style="color:#1C2C4F;font-family:'Noto Sans JP',sans-serif;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.15em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 8px 0;">The Fall from Grace</p>
						<p style="color:#1C2C4F;font-family:'Noto Serif JP',serif;font-size:15px;line-height:1.85;margin:0;"><strong>Social class defined who could play and when.</strong> As the Sanshin became associated with entertainment districts and lower social classes, it acquired a stigma. Playing the Sanshin was seen as the mark of someone without serious ambition — a "loser" in the eyes of respectable society.</p>
					</div>
					<div style="background:#fff;border-left:4px solid #8B1D25;padding:20px 24px;margin-bottom:16px;">
						<p style="color:#8B1D25;font-family:'Noto Sans JP',sans-serif;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.15em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 8px 0;">Cultural Reclamation</p>
						<p style="color:#1C2C4F;font-family:'Noto Serif JP',serif;font-size:15px;line-height:1.85;margin:0;"><strong>Today, the Sanshin is being reclaimed as a symbol of pride.</strong> Modern musicians and cultural activists have transformed the instrument's image from "loser instrument" to cultural treasure. It now represents resilience, identity, and the power of reclaiming marginalized traditions.</p>
					</div>
					<div style="background:#fff;border-left:4px solid #1C2C4F;padding:20px 24px;margin-bottom:40px;">
						<p style="color:#1C2C4F;font-family:'Noto Sans JP',sans-serif;font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.15em;text-transform:uppercase;margin:0 0 8px 0;">A Living Tradition</p>
						<p style="color:#1C2C4F;font-family:'Noto Serif JP',serif;font-size:15px;line-height:1.85;margin:0;"><strong>The Sanshin is more alive than ever.</strong> Recognized as part of UNESCO's Intangible Cultural Heritage, it is central to Okinawan music festivals, taught to new generations, and serves as a bridge between ancient tradition and contemporary expression.</p>
					</div>

					<h2 style="font-family:'Shippori Mincho','Noto Serif JP',serif;font-size:22px;font-weight:700;color:#1C2C4F;margin:0 0 20px 0;padding-top:8px;border-top:2px solid #D0C5BA;">Why This Story Matters</h2>
					<p style="margin:0 0 24px 0;">
						The Sanshin's journey from stigma to symbol of pride mirrors the broader Okinawan experience — a culture that has been suppressed, dismissed, and marginalized, yet refuses to disappear. Every note played on the Sanshin today is an act of cultural resistance.
					</p>
					<p style="margin:0;">
						When you hear the Sanshin, you're not just hearing music. You're hearing a people's refusal to be silenced.
					</p>

				</div>

				<!-- CTA -->
				<div style="margin-top:64px;background:#1C2C4F;padding:48px;border-top:4px solid #8B1D25;text-align:center;">
